author: Chandrima Banerjee
title: What we know about the genome of the virus in India
description: India News: A mutation unique to Indian samples of SARS-CoV2 virus could hold the key to the response to the Covid-19 outbreak in the country
content:
Mutations in Indian genome
Spike surface glycoprotein (unique to India): A virus protein which helps a virus attach itself to a host cell and enter it
